ScenePlay — quick start
=======================

ScenePlay turns one computer (a Raspberry Pi or any Linux box — Windows works
too) into an atmosphere controller for tabletop gaming: music, video, LED
lighting and a full TTRPG toolkit, all controlled from any browser on your
network (phone, tablet, laptop).

Full, beginner-friendly install instructions live in README.md — read that
first. The short version:

Linux / Raspberry Pi
--------------------
1. Open a Terminal.
2. sudo visudo   → add at the bottom (your username instead of sammy):
       sammy  ALL=(ALL) NOPASSWD:ALL
   save with Ctrl+X, Y, Enter.
3. cd ~
   git clone https://github.com/ScenePlay/ScenePlay_Flask_Media_Wrapper ScenePlay
4. cd ~/ScenePlay
   chmod +x requirements.sh
   ./requirements.sh        (takes a while; sets up auto-start on boot)
   sudo reboot
5. From any device on the same network open:
       http://<server-ip>             (find the ip with: hostname -I)
   No port needed — the installer sets up nginx on the normal web port.
   Fallback if that doesn't respond: http://<server-ip>:8086

Windows
-------
1. Download the project (green Code button → Download ZIP → Extract All),
   put the folder somewhere permanent.
2. Double-click install.bat and follow the prompts (if it asks you to re-run
   it, close the window and double-click it again).
3. Double-click startApp.bat, allow it through the firewall if asked, then
   open http://localhost:8086

Importing music/video from YouTube
----------------------------------
Use the Utilities page, or install the browser extension (see "Browser
extensions" in README.md): chrome://extensions → Developer mode →
Load unpacked → select the ChromeExt folder. The extension works on YouTube
pages and sends the video straight to your server.

Have fun. Don't Panic!!
